         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21 March 1894. ¶  ¶ The small clover, of which your son Wilhelm ¶  sent specimens, dear Clara, is "the  ¶ annual ¶  strawberry clover,  ¶ Trifolium resupinatum ¶ ." It is a useful pasture herb, and fo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">94.03.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Clara Wehl</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">21/3/94</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Der kleine Klee, von dem Dein Sohn Wilhelm Exemplare sandte, liebe Clara, ist "the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annual</hi>
               </seg> strawberry-clover, <name key="Trifolium%20resupinatum">Trifolium resupinatum</name>." Es ist ein nützliches Weidekraut, u ich habe es daher auch in mein Werk "Select plants" aufgenommen. Vielleicht hast Du aber keine der neueren Ausgaben des Werks. Samen sind nicht käuflich, aber da es reichlich trägt, lassen sich ja bald genug Samen dort erlangen zum weitern Aussäen. Die Pflanze verbreitet sich aber auch leicht ohne Cultur. Ich möchte gern Deines Sohnes Ansichten wissen über den <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dortigen</hi>
               </seg> Werth der Pflanze. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Dein</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Dieser Klee ist wild am mittelländischen Meere.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21 March 1894.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The small clover, of which your son Wilhelm<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. William Mueller Wehl, farming at Millicent, SA at this time (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Border watch</seg> (Mt Gambier), 21 April 1894, p. 3), and was a director of a frozen meat company.</p>
               </note> sent specimens, dear Clara, is "the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annual</hi>
               </seg> strawberry clover, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Trifolium%20resupinatum">Trifolium resupinatum</name>
               </seg>." It is a useful pasture herb, and for that reason I have also included it in my work <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Select extra-tropical plants</seg>. Perhaps you do not have one of the more recent editions of the work.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The most recent (eighth) edition was B91.09.01. </p>
               </note> Seeds cannot be purchased, but as it bears heavily, enough seeds can soon be obtained for further sowing. But the plant also spreads easily without culture. I should like to know your son's opinion on the value of the plant <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">there</hi>
               </seg>. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">This clover grows wild at the Mediterranean.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Trifolium%20resupinatum">Trifolium resupinatum</name>
            </p>
         </div>
